The optical system of claim 1 further comprising in order from the object side to the image side:
a first lens (110), which is positive meniscus and concave to the object side;
a second lens (120), which is negative meniscus and concave to the object side;
a third lens (130), which is negative meniscus and convex to the object side;
a fourth lens (140), which is biconvex; and,
a fifth lens (150), which is negative meniscus and concave to the object side.

The optical system of claim 1 further comprising in order from the object side to the image side:
a first lens (210), which is positive meniscus and convex to the object side;
a second lens (220), which is positive meniscus and concave to the object side;
a third lens (230), which is negative meniscus and concave to the object side;
a fourth lens (240), which is biconvex; and,
a fifth lens (250), which is negative meniscus and concave to the object side.

The optical system of claim 1 further comprising in order from the object side to the image side:
a first lens (310), which is negative meniscus and convex to the object side;
a second lens (320), which is positive meniscus and convex to the object side;
a third lens (330), which is positive meniscus and concave to the object side;
a fourth lens (340), which is biconvex and has a greater convexity to the object side; and,
a fifth lens (350), which is negative meniscus and concave to the object side.

The optical system of claim 11, further comprising in order from the object side to the image side:
a fourth lens (440), which is plano-convex and planar to the object side;
a fifth lens (450), which is biconvex;
