a seventh lens (470), which is negative meniscus and concave to the object side;
an eighth lens (480), which is biconvex; and,
a ninth lens (490), which is negative meniscus and concave to the object side.

An optical system which is correctible for all third order aberrations and all fifth order aberrations, having an object side and an image side, and comprising in order from the object side to the image side:
a first lens (510), which is negative meniscus and convex to the object side;
a second lens (520), which is negative meniscus and convex to the object side;
a third lens (530), which is positive meniscus and convex to the object side;
a fourth lens (540), which is biconvex and has a lesser convexity to the object side;
a fifth lens (550), which is negative meniscus and concave to the object side; and,
a sixth lens (560), which is plano-concave and concave to the object side.

The optical system of claim 1 further comprising in order from the object side to the image side:
a first lens (610), which is biconvex;
a second lens (620), which is negative meniscus and concave to the object side;
a third lens (630), which is positive meniscus and concave to the object side; and,
